issue.body:
Signed-off-by: Igor Bezukh <ibezukh@redhat.com>

Runbook PR: https://github.com/openshift/runbooks/pull/318

**What this PR does / why we need it**:
In an upgrade scenario it can happen that duplicate wasp-agent
deployment can appear, since previous wasp-agent deployments
were manual and in a different namespace.
Therefore in order to make sure the user is aware of it we
are adding an alert which will rely on the a metric of memory
overcommit percentage and presence of wasp namespace.

refactor(e2e): Replace fixed sleeps with dynamic wait helpers

Eliminates the use of `asyncio.sleep()` in end-to-end tests to prevent flaky test failures caused by timing issues on different environments.

This is achieved by introducing event-driven async helper functions that dynamically wait for specific conditions to be met before proceeding.

Key changes:
- A new `tests/e2e/helpers.py` module is introduced to house common wait logic.
  - `wait_for_log()`: Waits for a specific message to appear in the subprocess stdout/stderr.
  - `wait_for_webhook()`: Waits for a certain number of requests to be received by the test webhook server.
  - `wait_for_mqtt_message()`: Waits for an MQTT message on a specific topic.
- `test_mqtt_log`, `test_mqtt_webhook`, and `test_mqtt_mqtt_publish` are refactored to use these new helpers instead of a fixed `asyncio.sleep()`.

pull_request.title: feat: Add Basic AI Tool Integration
pull_request.body:
# Add Basic AI Tool Integration

This PR implements the basic AI tool integration feature as specified in issue #4, focusing on the nocodo CLI as the primary interface for AI tools, with Manager providing coordination.

## What's Implemented

âœ… **nocodo CLI**: Implement `nocodo session <tool> <prompt>` command
âœ… **Manager**: Unix socket server for CLI communication
âœ… **CLI-to-Manager**: Context request protocol (project info, file data)
âœ… **Manager**: Session tracking and coordination
âœ… **Error Handling**: CLI failures, Manager unavailable, AI tool not found

## Technical Details

### New Components Added:

1. **Unix Socket Communication**:
   - Manager daemon listens on `/tmp/nocodo-manager.sock`
   - CLI client connects via Unix socket for session requests
   - Structured JSON request/response protocol

2. **AI Session Database Schema**:
   - New `ai_sessions` table with session tracking
   - Stores tool name, status, prompt, project context
   - Links to projects table for context

3. **Session Command**:
   - `nocodo session claude "add authentication to this project"`
   - Supports multiple AI tools: claude, gemini, openai
   - Enhanced prompts with project context from Manager

4. **Project Context Integration**:
   - Manager provides project-specific context to AI tools
   - Path-based project detection and context generation
   - Session completion/failure tracking

### Flow Implementation:

```
AI Tool â†’ nocodo CLI â†’ Manager Daemon â†’ Context/Project Data
```

The CLI acts as the primary interface, communicating with Manager via Unix socket to get project context and track AI sessions.

## Usage

After starting the Manager daemon:

```bash
# Start Manager daemon
nocodo-manager --config ~/.config/nocodo/manager.toml

# Start AI session with enhanced context
nocodo session claude "refactor the user authentication system"
nocodo session gemini "add unit tests for the API endpoints" 
nocodo session openai "optimize the database queries"
```

## Testing Notes

The implementation includes:
- Error handling for Manager unavailable scenarios
- Tool availability checking before execution  
- Session tracking with completion/failure states
- Enhanced prompts with project context
- Structured logging throughout the flow

## Dependencies

This builds on:
- âœ… Issue #1 (Manager Daemon) - Unix socket server functionality
- âœ… Issue #3 (CLI Analysis) - Base CLI functionality

Ready for manual testing - the Manager daemon and CLI components compile successfully. End-to-end testing can be performed with actual AI tools installed.

## Next Steps

After merge and manual testing:
- End-to-end testing with actual AI tools
- Web interface integration for AI sessions
- Advanced context analysis and guardrails
- Multi-project session management

Hi,

## Bug Description
On windows kokoro-tts doesn't run without voices-v1.0.bin

## Steps to Reproduce
1. Go to 'C:\Users\User' (My case)
2. replace  voices-v1.0.bin with both files 1) voices.json 2) kokoro-v1.0.onnx
3. Enter command 'c:/temp/ebook.epub --split-output c:/temp/chapters/ --format mp3 --lang it --voice im_nicola'
4. See error 

P.S. the Italian voice has a strong English accent

## Expected Behavior
run without problems  

## Actual Behavior
Error loading Kokoro model: Voices file not found at voices-v1.0.bin
You can download the voices file using the following command:
wget https://github.com/thewh1teagle/kokoro-onnx/releases/download/model-files-v1.0/voices-v1.0.bin

## Environment
- OS: Windows 11
- Python version: 3.12
- Voice model version:  kokoro-v1.0.onnx, voices.json,voices-v1.0.bin
- Input format: EPUB

## Problem Addressed

Issue #809 required comprehensive validation enhancements to the CI pipeline to:

- Ensure robust LaTeX package dependency handling (specifically for the `pifont` package)
- Create validation steps that run before LaTeX compilation
- Enhance error detection to catch configuration issues early

1. **Comprehensive Validation Test Suite** (`test_issue_743_validation.py`)

   - CTMM build system integration testing
   - Form elements integration validation

2. **Enhanced GitHub Actions Workflow** (`.github/workflows/latex-build.yml`)

# Fix parts detail data mapping with hybrid approach ## Summary This PR fixes a regression introduced in PR #3 where clicking the "éƒ¨å“è©³ç´°" (Parts Detail) button from the main table resulted in a "è©²å½“ãƒ‡ãƒ¼ã‚¿ã®æ˜Žç´°ãŒè¦‹ã¤ã‹ã‚Šã¾ã›ã‚“ã§ã—ãŸã€‚" (No corresponding data details found) error message and blank page. **Root Cause**: The previous fix removed the `findOrder()` function and replaced it with direct array indexing by `rowIndex`. However, the `normalize()` function in `SevenFieldsTable.tsx` transforms raw `uploaded-json` data into `working-rows-v1` format, stripping out parts arrays via `pickSevenFromOrder()`. This broke the 1:1 index correspondence between the two localStorage data structures. **Solution**: Implemented a hybrid data retrieval approach that: 1. **Restores the `findOrder()` function** for field matching on ["å—æ³¨ç•ªå·", "ç´å…¥å…ˆç•ªå·", "å‡ºè·æ—¥"] 2. **Adds `getPartsForRow()` hybrid function** that tries direct indexing first (performance), falls back to field matching (reliability) 3. **Updates component state** to track both `rowIndex` (from URL) and `selectedRow` (from localStorage) 4. **Updates data flow logic** in `details` useMemo and `modifyTargetOrder` function to use hybrid approach ## Review & Testing Checklist for Human - [ ] **Test core functionality**: Click "éƒ¨å“è©³ç´°" buttons from main table for multiple rows, verify no errors and correct parts data displays - [ ] **Test edit functionality**: Edit part values (éƒ¨å“ç•ªå·, éƒ¨å“å, æ•°é‡, å£²ä¸Šå˜ä¾¡) and verify changes persist correctly - [ ] **Test delete functionality**: Delete parts and verify data is properly removed from underlying storage - [ ] **Test with different data structures**: If possible, test with different data sets to ensure hybrid approach handles various formats - [ ] **Check browser console**: Verify no JavaScript errors during navigation and data operations **Recommended End-to-End Test Plan**: Load the application â†’ Upload/process data â†’ Navigate through main table rows using "éƒ¨å“è©³ç´°" buttons â†’ Edit some part values â†’ Delete some parts â†’ Navigate back to main table â†’ Verify all changes persisted correctly. --- ### Diagram ```mermaid %%{ init : { "theme" : "default" }}%% flowchart TD MainTable["src/app/components/
SevenFieldsTable.tsx"]:::context DetailPage["src/app/detail/
page.tsx"]:::major-edit LocalStorage1["localStorage
uploaded-json
(raw data with parts)"]:::context LocalStorage2["localStorage
working-rows-v1
(normalized 7 fields)"]:::context LocalStorage3["localStorage
selected-row
(current selection)"]:::context MainTable -->|"handleOpenParts()
sets selected-row
navigates to /detail?i=X"| DetailPage DetailPage -->|"reads raw data
with parts arrays"| LocalStorage1 DetailPage -->|"reads current
row selection"| LocalStorage3 DetailPage -->|"hybrid approach:
direct index + field matching"| LocalStorage2 subgraph "New Hybrid Functions" FindOrder["findOrder()
(restored)"]:::major-edit GetParts["getPartsForRow()
(new hybrid)"]:::major-edit end DetailPage --> FindOrder DetailPage --> GetParts subgraph Legend L1["Major Edit"]:::major-edit L2["Minor Edit"]:::minor-edit L3["Context/No Edit"]:::context end classDef major-edit fill:#90EE90 classDef minor-edit fill:#87CEEB classDef context fill:#FFFFFF ``` ### Notes - **Environment Sensitivity**: The original issue only manifested in the user's environment, suggesting potential data structure variations that the hybrid approach should handle more robustly - **Data Structure Complexity**: The system handles both legacy format (parts in `æ˜Žç´°` array) and new format (separate arrays for each field), plus the normalization process that strips parts data - **Performance vs Reliability Trade-off**: Direct indexing is faster but fragile; field matching is slower but more reliable across different data structures - **Lint Issues**: Some pre-existing TypeScript lint warnings remain in the restored `findOrder()` function but are not related to the core functionality fix **Session Details**: - Link to Devin run: https://app.devin.ai/sessions/9ccd62075abe477aac596b39dd55ee59 - Requested by: è¡£æ–å¸éƒŽ (@shiro-mail) - Browser testing confirmed fix works across multiple rows (i=0, i=1, i=2) with correct parts data display

issue.title: Support C++ private: class members with getter() functions
issue.body:
### Description:
<!-- Provide a description of what you want to happen here -->
Ideally, a Base class should have `private:` rather than `protected:` class members, with a protected or even public function used as an accessor. This is particularly true for generated classes where the class members are normally pointers that a derived class can get() but should not set().

Right now there isn't any way to do this because there is no `private:` option in the class access drop-down list. There is a way for a dev to add their own getter function, but without the `private:` option, it's useless as a getter function.

## Design change

1) Add `private:` to the drop-down list. Note that this isn't required for non-derived classes which have the option of converting all `protected:` members to `private:' but it would avoid potential confusion.
2) Add a getter() function below the class access that is disabled unless class access is set to `private:'. The getter() function would be added as a `protected:` function. Note that we would need to verify uniqueness of the function name across the entire form, including any class methods the dev may have added to the form.

Update selective checks to run core tests when serialization files changes (#54423)

Remove SDK BaseOperator in TaskInstance (#53223)

Co-authored-by: Kaxil Naik <kaxilnaik@gmail.com>

Remove dag_id from Deadline table (#54281)

Since we have dagrun_id in the Deadline table, we don't need the dag_id
to look up the associated Dag. So, this will improve database
normalization.

test(cli): add consistency check for variables import help message formats (#54222)

Co-authored-by: Evgenii Prusov <evgenii@DSE-PF4Z9L6S.Dsg2ic.com>

Remove support for re-serializing a Serialized Operator (#54428)

Bringing https://github.com/apache/airflow/pull/53340 back but only for removing Reserialized BaseOp.

Prevent repeated warning of triggers being added twice in triggerer (#54438)

When running multiple deferrable in parallel, triggers are repeatedly
added to triggerer queue to create by the update_trigger's method. Then it's
being skipped with a warning at the creating_trigger's method. The
warning is too many when there're many tasks to defer causing inefficency.

The fix here was to exclude the already queued triggers from the triggers to
create and I purposely left the warning log of encountering a trigger already
in to_create in case there's another way it could still be possible.
Create FAB's user/role tables on migration, not only on initdb (#54227)

Explicitly set the JWTGenerator private_key field to None for service logs retrieval (#54442)

In a recent change, the private_key parameter is left empty when instantiating the JWTGenerator used to authenticate log serving requests for in-progress tasks. Such requests use the shared secret_key instead. However, leaving private_key unset means that it is automatically populated through the attrs field factory and this leads to a failure in the post init which asserts mutual exclusivity of secret_key and private_key. The result is stack traces in the API Server logs like the following when retrieving "live" logs:

```
[2025-08-12T19:33:59.403+0000] {file_task_handler.py:907} ERROR - Could not read served logs
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "/usr/local/lib/python3.12/site-packages/airflow/utils/log/file_task_handler.py", line 878, in _read_from_logs_server
    response = _fetch_logs_from_service(url, rel_path)
               ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
  File "/usr/local/lib/python3.12/site-packages/airflow/utils/log/file_task_handler.py", line 173, in _fetch_logs_from_service
    generator = JWTGenerator(
                ^^^^^^^^^^^^^
  File "<attrs generated methods airflow.api_fastapi.auth.tokens.JWTGenerator>", line 34, in __init__
    self.__attrs_post_init__()
  File "/usr/local/lib/python3.12/site-packages/airflow/api_fastapi/auth/tokens.py", line 417, in __attrs_post_init__
    raise ValueError("Exactly one of private_key and secret_key must be specified")
ValueError: Exactly one of private_key and secret_key must be specified
```

The fix is to add back the explicit `private_key=None`, for which we have to add a mypy type ignore comment as it does not seem to understand that `None` is allowed for `AllowedPrivateKeys | None`.

Redirects 404 fix #54255 (#54407)

* redirects for issue 54255

* git test

* test commit

Ensure TaskInstance.end_date and duration are populated before invoking failure callbacks (#52729)

* Fix: Set TaskInstance end_date before failure callbacks (#52630)

- Set ti.end_date before creating TaskState in exception handlers
- Ensures on_failure_callback context has proper end_date and duration
- Fixes race condition where callbacks received incomplete TaskInstance data
- Add test to verify callback context contains required timing information

* Enhance task callbacks to include end_date and duration metrics
Remove timeout from airflow.utils and update core usages accordingly (#54212)

Handle overflow in TaskInstance `next_retry_datetime` (#48557)

This handles overflow when calculating the next execution time for a task instance by falling back to the configured maximum delay. The solution uses the same strategy that tenacity uses:
https://github.com/jd/tenacity/blob/main/tenacity/wait.py#L167

An alternate solution would be the determine the maximum tries that wouldn't exceed the maximum delay and then not calculate the timeout for values larger than that.

Something like 

```
max_delay = self.task.max_retry_delay if self.task.max_retry_delay is not null else MAX_RETRY_DELAY
tries_before_max_delay = math.floor(math.log2(max_delay))
if self.try_number <= tries_before_max_delay:
     # existing logic
else:
    delay = max_delay
```

closes: https://github.com/apache/airflow/issues/47971
Refactor example task to use context and logging for parameter access (#54450)

Add ordering to AssetEvent query in SchedulerJobRunner (#52231)

closes: #52230 

This change is adding ordering for selecting asset events to maintain the ordering.

fix map_index is null dynamic task mapping bug (#54249) closes: #52881 ### Problem Description When tasks within nested task groups try to access XCom values from sibling tasks in the same mapped parent task group instance, the system incorrectly uses `map_index=null` instead of the correct map index, causing XCom lookup failures. ##### Example DAG Structure ##### Error Observed (Note: map_index=null) ```javascript No XCom value found; defaulting to None.: key="return_value": dag_id="test_dag": task_id="expandable_task_group.inner_task_group.alter_input": run_id="manual__2025-07-04T14:56:47.815002+00:00": map_index=null ``` ##### Related Code The issue is in `airflow-core/src/airflow/api_fastapi/execution_api/routes/task_instances.py` in the `_get_upstream_map_indexes` function. The logic only checks the immediate parent task group (upstream_task.task_group) but doesn't consider nested scenarios where tasks are within a regular task group that is itself within a mapped task group. ##### Proposed Solution Replace the immediate parent check with a hierarchy-aware check using `get_closest_mapped_task_group()`. This ensures that both tasks recognize they share the same mapped task group ancestor and use the same map_index. ### Testing - Verified proposed solution resolves issue: #52881 when tested locally using `breeze start-airflow` against the latest main branch development environment. - Added `test_nested_mapped_task_group_upstream_indexes` to verify that tasks in nested mapped task groups correctly resolve upstream map indexes.

Hide individual Public Interface subsections from sidebar navigation (#54457)

* Hide individual Public Interface subsections from sidebar navigation

* Revert "Hide individual Public Interface subsections from sidebar navigation"

This reverts commit 3ee5448b6126f3f3f74e25a59bb7ef2d81019611.

* Fix sidebar navigation to collapse Public Interface subsections by default

Bump `zizmor` pre-commit to fix static checks (#54468)

Example failure: https://github.com/apache/airflow/actions/runs/16939729227/job/48005461746?pr=54467

new version was cut 40 mins ago: https://github.com/zizmorcore/zizmor-pre-commit/releases/tag/v1.12.0

Fix missing expand/collapse buttons in Grid view using shared group sync hook (#53919) (#54257)

* refactor: moved shared graph structure sync logic to new useGraphStructureSync.ts hook for reuse in Grid and Graph files

* used shared hook in Grid and Graph files and updated related variables

* Optimized group IDs comparison and suppressed unused hook return warning

* Moved task group syncing logic into OpenGroupsProvider so it runs for both
views automatically and reverted the changes for graph and grid views.

* removed hook file as code has been updated in opengroupProvider.tsx file

Better handling missing airflow package doc inventories (#54464)

When airflow package inventories cannot be downloaded (for example
because they were deleted) we can always rebuild them locally from
sources. This might happen for example when our "main" developer
documentation published in `apache-airflow-docs` is accidentally
or purposefully deleted (for example to refresh it from scratch).

This can also happen when we have a new provider and it has never
been published, or when we add new distribution that has not yet
had a documentation built (such as task-sdk, or airflowctl in
the future).

This PR updates the existing mechanism to:

* not only handle missing "apache-airflow-" packages but also the
  other airflow packages that do not follow this naming convention

* adds better diagnostics so that if we miss to add a distribution
  in the future we know what to do

However, the `normalize()` function in `SevenFieldsTable.tsx` transforms raw `uploaded-json` data into `working-rows-v1` format, stripping out parts arrays via `pickSevenFromOrder()`. This broke the 1:1 index correspondence between the two localStorage data structures. **Solution**: Implemented a hybrid data retrieval approach that: 1. **Restores the `findOrder()` function** for field matching on ["å—æ³¨ç•ªå·", "ç´å…¥å…ˆç•ªå·", "å‡ºè·æ—¥"] 2. **Adds `getPartsForRow()` hybrid function** that tries direct indexing first (performance), falls back to field matching (reliability) 3. **Updates component state** to track both `rowIndex` (from URL) and `selectedRow` (from localStorage) 4. **Updates data flow logic** in `details` useMemo and `modifyTargetOrder` function to use hybrid approach ## Review & Testing Checklist for Human - [ ] **Test core functionality**: Click "éƒ¨å“è©³ç´°" buttons from main table for multiple rows, verify no errors and correct parts data displays - [ ] **Test edit functionality**: Edit part values (éƒ¨å“ç•ªå·, éƒ¨å“å, æ•°é‡, å£²ä¸Šå˜ä¾¡) and verify changes persist correctly - [ ] **Test delete functionality**: Delete parts and verify data is properly removed from underlying storage - [ ] **Test with different data structures**: If possible, test with different data sets to ensure hybrid approach handles various formats - [ ] **Check browser console**: Verify no JavaScript errors during navigation and data operations **Recommended End-to-End Test Plan**: Load the application â†’ Upload/process data â†’ Navigate through main table rows using "éƒ¨å“è©³ç´°" buttons â†’ Edit some part values â†’ Delete some parts â†’ Navigate back to main table â†’ Verify all changes persisted correctly. --- ### Diagram ```mermaid %%{ init : { "theme" : "default" }}%% flowchart TD MainTable["src/app/components/

pull_request.title: Fix: clear duplicate-casing errors after case-only file renames on Windows (closes #261995)
pull_request.body: On case-insensitive file systems (Windows for example) renaming a file by only changing its letter-case ~ for example `page1.js` => `Page1.js` ~ confuses `tsserver`. It continues to hold both casings in the program and surfaces errors such as: The error persists until the user manually restarts the TS server or reloads VS Code (see bug #261995). ### RCA File-watcher stacks donâ€™t always emit a delete => create sequence for a case-only rename on case-insensitive FSs. `tsserver` therefore never drops the old path and thinks the file is duplicated. ### Testing * Verified on Windows 11. ### Files changed * `extensions/typescript-language-features/src/languageFeatures/updatePathsOnRename.ts` * `extensions/typescript-language-features/src/typeScriptServiceClientHost.ts` --- Closes #261995
